# FIXME: test's `alloc_random_tables` can request `calloc(8 << bitsleft)` where
# bitsleft up to 22 (= 16 MB single allocation).  Available heap is bounded by
# the monitor-space ceiling (0xffffffff - 0xff022540 ~= 16 MB).  A 4 MB heap
# override passes with TEST_ITERATIONS=10 but fails with the default 10000
# because the RNG occasionally requests larger allocations.  To make the test
# pass at 10000 iterations we'd need either a much lower link address or a
# test-side cap on table size.
# ./kernel/mem/varadix/test

